    "notes": "High-fidelity signal: w3wp.exe (IIS worker) spawning any child process is abnormal and high-confidence exploitation. Chain: w3wp.exe writes executable to ProgramData -> launches it -> it beacons outbound. Differentiate from benign by: (1) parent process context (services.exe vs w3wp.exe), (2) user context (SYSTEM vs IUSR/IIS APPPOOL), (3) file drop path (signed vendor path vs ProgramData\\WindowsUpdate), (4) destination IP reputation (Microsoft RDFE 168.63.129.16 vs unknown Tor-exit 185.220.101.x). Detection rule should alert on: w3wp.exe, java.exe, tomcat*.exe, or python.exe as parent of any non-IIS binary."
